                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/407.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department has received a telegram from Chiarí, to the following effect:
                    “Constituted authorities, in league with largely increased body of policemen
                    armed with rifles, terrorize citizens, put them in jail without any cause or
                    trial, attack and even murder them. Personal liberty and security do not exist.
                    Complaints to governor have no effect. American intervention should be extended
                    to control police, otherwise public peace may be disturbed at any moment.”
                    Department has replied: “The complaint contained in your telegram of yesterday
                    would seem to be a matter proper to be laid before the supervision
                    committee.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
